comments.body:
You're getting output from both programs at the same time because your cmdlet isn't waiting for the editor to exit. Calling `Start()` on the `Process` class is non-blocking. The editor starts and PowerShell keeps on going. If you change your code to capture the the process object then call `.WaitForExit()` you should be fine:
``` 
var proc = System.Diagnostics.Process.Start("/bin/vim", "/home/nutanix/asdf");
proc.WaitForExit();
```
